In anticipation of next week&rsquo;s Reproducible Science Hackathon at NESCent, I was thinking about Christie Bahlai&rsquo;s post on &ldquo;Baby steps for the open-curious.&rdquo;
Moving from Ye Olde Standard Computational Science Practice to a fully reproducible workflow seems a monumental task, but partially reproducible is better than not-at-all reproducible, and it&rsquo;d be good to give people some advice on how to get started - to encourage them to get started.
So, I spent some time today writing another of my minimal tutorials, on initial steps towards reproducible research.

Yesterday, I saw this tweet by @Ananyo
